<div id="review_1178469067" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1178469067" />
    <a title="Melanie Marsh" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/8058065-melanie-marsh"><img alt="Melanie Marsh" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1333745151p2/8058065.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1178469067?book_show_action=true">Jan 23, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Melanie Marsh" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Melanie Marsh" href="/user/show/8058065-melanie-marsh">Melanie Marsh</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781620155950" href="/book/show/23935117-blood-spirits">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1178469067" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3152480651336175820">Blood and Spirits turned out to be a pleasant surprise. I expected it to be entertaining, as I do any book I read, but I didnâ€™t necessarily expect it to blow me away. But it totally did! I love it when I get more than I expected instead of less! <br/><br/>There are so many great things about this book that Iâ€™m having trouble deciding where to start. So Iâ€™ll start at the beginning. The cover of this book is totally bad ass. I absolutely love it. I know that we arenâ€™t supposed to judge a book by its cover, </span>
  <span id="freeText3152480651336175820" style="display:none">Blood and Spirits turned out to be a pleasant surprise. I expected it to be entertaining, as I do any book I read, but I didnâ€™t necessarily expect it to blow me away. But it totally did! I love it when I get more than I expected instead of less! <br /><br />There are so many great things about this book that Iâ€™m having trouble deciding where to start. So Iâ€™ll start at the beginning. The cover of this book is totally bad ass. I absolutely love it. I know that we arenâ€™t supposed to judge a book by its cover, but whom are we kidding really? We both know we are more likely to read a book with a cool cover than a book without one. <br /><br />Veronica is a vampire Madam. As in prostitutes. As in she runs a brothel. And sheâ€™s a vampire. She sounds SMOKING hot, as I think vampires should. Apparently, she has some enemies and such, so this book focuses on one of those enemies and the nastiness they are trying to get away with. <br /><br />Blood and Spirits isnâ€™t a one-dimensional book, by any means. It has multiple layers, and different concepts throughout the book and really keeps you guessing as to what is going to come next. There are multiple conflicts, peaks, and resolutions so the story continues through several well set scenarios. I like how the author sets everything up for explanation and back story throughout the book. There is a variety of paranormal elements and species to give the story a more complex world in which Veronica and friends reside. <br /><br />There is one thing with which I had a small problem. At one point Veronica is telling the story of what has happened to cause her to feel the need to involve Julius, her maker. She is telling it to him so that he can â€œseeâ€ her memories. This goes on for quite a while so at some point, I realized that I forgot what going on and the role Julius was playing. I asked myself, â€œWhy did she go pick him up? Where is he now?â€ At that point, I remembered what was going on, but for a minute, I was confused. <br /> <br />Iâ€™m not going to lie, at first, I was surprised that this book was written by a man. I had actually forgotten who wrote it while I was reading it, as thatâ€™s not necessarily something I think about. For whatever reason, in my head, I had assumed Blood and Spirits was written by a woman. When I realized Dennis Sharpe wrote it, who, I am under the impression, is NOT a woman, I was surprised until I started to think more about it. He pulled off something many men cannot. He wrote a book from a femaleâ€™s perspective and didnâ€™t completely screw it up. His action scenes were well thought out and planned. Veronica kicks ass all over the place and she looks good doing it. Iâ€™m pretty sure itâ€™s a fantasy for some men to see a super hot chick kicking ass. <br /><br />Regardless of the authorâ€™s sex, this was a great book. There was action, emotion, mystery, multiple paranormal and horror-esq elements that all came together to create a wonderful book that I will recommend to anyone who likes female Vampires who can kick the crap out of people both physically AND mentally! I highly recommend this book to all vampire lovers out there. <br /></span>
